<section class="app-page-shell platform-guide-shell">
    <section class="app-page-header platform-guide-hero">
        <div class="platform-guide-copy">
            <p class="platform-guide-eyebrow">Student Guide</p>
            <h1>How students move from public learning content into class activity and academic updates.</h1>
            <p class="platform-guide-lead">
                This guide explains the student-facing path from lesson discovery to dashboards, activities, attendance, and grade-related visibility.
            </p>
            <div class="platform-guide-actions">
                <a href="/lessons" class="platform-guide-btn platform-guide-btn-primary">Browse Lessons</a>
                <a href="/how-it-works" class="platform-guide-btn platform-guide-btn-secondary">How It Works</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="platform-guide-note">
            <p class="platform-guide-note-label">Student Path</p>
            <h2>Main student experience</h2>
            <ul class="platform-guide-note-list">
                <li>Discover lessons and learning resources</li>
                <li>Join classes and open assigned activities</li>
                <li>Track updates, attendance, and academic records</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="platform-guide-grid">
        <article class="app-panel platform-guide-panel">
            <p class="platform-guide-section-eyebrow">Student Workflow</p>
            <h2>What the student-facing journey looks like</h2>
            <div class="platform-guide-step-list">
                <article class="platform-guide-step">
                    <h3>1. Start with public resources</h3>
                    <p>Students can begin with lessons, help pages, and public articles before signing in, which makes the site useful even at first visit.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="platform-guide-step">
                    <h3>2. Access the student workspace</h3>
                    <p>After sign-in, students land in a role-aware dashboard rather than a generic shared account page.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="platform-guide-step">
                    <h3>3. Join and open classes</h3>
                    <p>Joined classes expose announcements, learning materials, and assigned work through a clearer class-specific flow.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="platform-guide-step">
                    <h3>4. Work through activities and quizzes</h3>
                    <p>Students can see status such as not started, in progress, submitted, late, and overdue while moving through assigned activities.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="platform-guide-step">
                    <h3>5. Check attendance and grade-related views</h3>
                    <p>The student side also includes attendance visibility and current academic-record views through the existing grade-related flows.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="app-panel app-panel-muted platform-guide-panel">
            <p class="platform-guide-section-eyebrow">Why this helps</p>
            <h2>One place instead of scattered academic pages</h2>
            <ul class="platform-guide-bullet-list">
                <li>Lessons, activities, and classes stay connected</li>
                <li>Announcements and updates are easier to follow</li>
                <li>Students can see progress without relying on multiple disconnected tools</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
    </section>
</section>
